  <!-- CASE STUDIES — detailed format -->
  <section style="padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--b-dim);">
    <div class="m-cases">

      <div class="m-case" data-reveal>
        <div class="m-case-num">Case 01</div>
        <div class="m-case-body">
          <h3>Marketplace Acceleration</h3>
          <p>A brand entered its first marketplace with a fragmented approach — uneven listings, no channel structure, and inconsistent execution. The problem was not the product. It was everything around it.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px;">I rebuilt the listing architecture, established a clear channel structure, and maintained execution consistency across eight months of scaling. The result was not luck — it was discipline applied to the right levers at the right time.</p>
          <div class="m-case-tags" style="margin-top: 28px;">
            <span class="m-tag">Amazon</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Listing architecture</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Channel structure</span>
            <span class="m-tag">8 months</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="m-case-meta">
          <div class="m-case-result">₹1.7 Cr</div>
          <div class="m-case-label">Revenue per month at peak</div>
          <div style="height: 1px; background: var(--b-dim); margin: 20px 0;"></div>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--t-lo); line-height: 1.7;">From launch to ₹1.7 Cr/month in 8 months through structural execution, not short-term tactics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="m-case" data-reveal>
        <div class="m-case-num">Case 02</div>
        <div class="m-case-body">
          <h3>Revenue Lift Through Tighter Execution</h3>
          <p>The business was generating ₹20L/month but growth had stalled. The founders were making decisions without a clear picture of what was actually working — and what was consuming margin without return.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px;">I restructured the decision flow, tightened execution across the growth levers, and improved the rhythm at which the team operated. Within 3 months, revenue had moved from ₹20L to ₹50L/month.</p>
          <div class="m-case-tags" style="margin-top: 28px;">
            <span class="m-tag">Decision flow</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Execution rhythm</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Revenue structure</span>
            <span class="m-tag">3 months</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="m-case-meta">
          <div class="m-case-result">₹20L→₹50L</div>
          <div class="m-case-label">Monthly revenue in 3 months</div>
          <div style="height: 1px; background: var(--b-dim); margin: 20px 0;"></div>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--t-lo); line-height: 1.7;">150% revenue lift. Not from a new channel — from better execution on what already existed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="m-case" data-reveal>
        <div class="m-case-num">Case 03</div>
        <div class="m-case-body">
          <h3>Backend Recovery & Control</h3>
          <p>The business was losing money it did not know it was losing. Sales data was fragmented, reconciliation was incomplete, and backend controls were soft. The exposure was significant — and growing.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px;">I introduced systematic reconciliation, tightened backend controls, and restructured how sales data was tracked and actioned. 95% reconciliation was achieved, and ₹10+ lakhs was recovered or saved.</p>
          <div class="m-case-tags" style="margin-top: 28px;">
            <span class="m-tag">Sales reconciliation</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Backend controls</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Financial discipline</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="m-case-meta">
          <div class="m-case-result">₹10L+</div>
          <div class="m-case-label">Recovered through backend controls</div>
          <div style="height: 1px; background: var(--b-dim); margin: 20px 0;"></div>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--t-lo); line-height: 1.7;">95% reconciliation rate. The money was already there — it just needed better systems to capture it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="m-case" data-reveal>
        <div class="m-case-num">Case 04</div>
        <div class="m-case-body">
          <h3>Revenue Generated From Ground Up</h3>
          <p>A business needed more than a growth plan — it needed a functioning operational foundation. Backend systems, warehouse coordination, and ERP execution were all underdeveloped. Growth could not happen without infrastructure.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px;">I led the ERP and warehouse execution layer from early implementation through to operational stability. The foundation held, and within 3 months the business was generating ₹25L/month in revenue.</p>
          <div class="m-case-tags" style="margin-top: 28px;">
            <span class="m-tag">ERP execution</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Warehouse operations</span>
            <span class="m-tag">Backend infrastructure</span>
            <span class="m-tag">3 months</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="m-case-meta">
          <div class="m-case-result">₹25L</div>
          <div class="m-case-label">Revenue generated per month in 3 months</div>
          <div style="height: 1px; background: var(--b-dim); margin: 20px 0;"></div>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--t-lo); line-height: 1.7;">Built the operational layer that made growth possible — then watched the revenue follow.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

